The paper discusses the design of hybrid precoders and combiners in mmWave MIMO systems, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and networking. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also addresses the hardware cost and power consumption issues, which are related to system design and control, suggesting cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible sub-category. Moreover, the paper focuses on the use of mmWave technology, which is a subfield of wireless communication and networking, indicating cs.MM (Multimedia) as a potential sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for binary analog precoder and combiner optimization, which involves optimization and search algorithms, suggesting cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as a possible sub-category.
